tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_ml_training_data (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  training_date DATE,
  dataset_name TEXT,
  features JSON,
  target_column TEXT,
  training_time DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE QuantumMachineLearningTrainingData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  training_data TEXT,
  training_timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ
)

CREATE TABLE ModelRetrainingData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  model_id INT,
  retraining_data TEXT,
  retraining_timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ
)

CREATE TABLE EvaluationData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  evaluation_id INT,
  evaluation_data TEXT,
  evaluation_timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ
)

CREATE TABLE training_metrics (
    metric_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    training_id INT,
    loss FLOAT,
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_training_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    training_accuracy FLOAT,
    test_accuracy FLOAT,
    loss FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_evaluation_metrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    evaluation_date TIMESTAMP,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
);
